&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://github.com/renard/o-blog"&gt; &lt;img
  style="position: fixed; top: 0; right: 0; border: 0; z-index: 999999;"
  src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_red_aa0000.png" alt="Fork me on GitHub"
  data-canonical-src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/github/ribbons/forkme_right_red_aa0000.png"&gt; &lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="jumbotron"&gt;
&lt;div class="page-header"&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;
o-blog &lt;small&gt;publication tool for emacs&lt;/small&gt;
&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="row"&gt;
&lt;div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4"&gt;
&lt;div class="thumbnail"&gt;
&lt;div class="caption"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;
Requirements
&lt;/h3&gt;
  
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emacs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;pandoc or org-mode&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;el-get or git&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4"&gt;
&lt;div class="thumbnail"&gt;
&lt;div class="caption"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;
Setup
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are using el-get it would be very easy to install. All you need to do is to add o-blog to el-get-sources and type:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;code&gt;M-x el-get-install o-blog&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="col-sm-6 col-md-4"&gt;
&lt;div class="thumbnail"&gt;
&lt;div class="caption"&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;
Publish
&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Only one single command:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;code&gt;M-x o-blog-publish&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class="alert alert-info"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that this site is for &lt;code&gt;o-blog 2&lt;/code&gt;. Old &lt;code&gt;o-blog&lt;/code&gt; versions is still available under the &lt;code&gt;o-blog-v1&lt;/code&gt; branch. &lt;code&gt;o-blog 2&lt;/code&gt; has been designed to be fully compatible with &lt;code&gt;o-blog 1&lt;/code&gt; but if you have compatibility problems please &lt;a href="https://github.com/renard/o-blog/issues"&gt;open an issue on Github&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
